parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked exhaust manifolds can cause exhaust gases to enter the driver's compartment, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning, which can be deadly.
symptoms: Ticking noise coming from the engine compartment
exhaust fumes leaking into the passenger compartment
decreased engine performance
stalling
and acceleration issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system failure can cause exhaust gases to leak into the passenger compartment, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning, and can also cause damage to other components, such as the air-ride suspension system.
symptoms: Exhaust breaking off at the mounting flange
melting of plastic components
and filling the cabin with melting plastic fumes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil fill spout failure can cause massive oil spills, leading to engine damage or even engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil spill
oil fill spout coming off the valve head cover
and poor glue quality.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Subframe and Suspension Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear subframe and suspension components can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in fires or fuel tank damage.
symptoms: Rear crossmember subframe rusting
control arm contacting fuel tank
loud noise
grinding noise
loss of vehicle stability
feeling of floating or tailspin
alignment issues
and pulling to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently when hitting bumps or potholes
the rack and pinion assembly needs to be replaced
the steering wheel electrical components fail
and the airbag light is constantly on despite no issues with the airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The radio and controls in the steering wheel fail
the horn stops working
the airbag light is constantly on
the driver-side window won't roll up or rolls down by itself
and the headlights have water in them.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The engine smokes excessively
and the vehicle shuts down multiple times without warning while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starting system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start if the front wheels are turned left or right when parked
and the steering wheel must be forced to align the wheels straight ahead to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down multiple times without warning while driving
and the transmission sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Brake Failure Due to Delta Sensor Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
braking is ineffective
the ABS system kicks in unnecessarily
the "BRAKE" light is illuminated
and the vehicle may shake or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Emergency Brake Cable Fracture
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake cable can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: A loud noise is heard
the vehicle loses control
and the emergency brake cable is fractured and wraps around the axle.
